</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[131,775,1069,1120]" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">
ILLUSTRATIONS. — Habitus: 
<bibRefCitation author="OTTE D. &amp; ALEXANDER R. D." box="[406,632,1069,1093]" pageId="37" pageNumber="442" pagination="1 - 477" refId="ref35794" refString="OTTE D. &amp; ALEXANDER R. D. 1983. - Australian crickets. Monographs of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 22: 1 - 477." type="journal article" year="1983">Otte &amp; Alexander 1983</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 268. Male genitalia: 
<bibRefCitation author="OTTE D. &amp; ALEXANDER R. D. &amp; CADE W." box="[225,381,1095,1120]" pageId="37" pageNumber="442" pagination="375 - 457" refId="ref35864" refString="OTTE D., ALEXANDER R. D. &amp; CADE W. 1987. - The Crickets of New Caledonia (Gryllidae). Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 139: 375 - 457." type="journal article" year="1987">
Otte 
<emphasis box="[277,324,1095,1119]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">et al.</emphasis>
1987
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 20C.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="442" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="37.[130,776,1143,1670]" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">
EMENDED DIAGNOSIS. — From 
<bibRefCitation author="OTTE D. &amp; ALEXANDER R. D." box="[437,683,1143,1167]" pageId="37" pageNumber="442" pagination="1 - 477" refId="ref35794" refString="OTTE D. &amp; ALEXANDER R. D. 1983. - Australian crickets. Monographs of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 22: 1 - 477." type="journal article" year="1983">Otte &amp; Alexander (1983)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="OTTE D. &amp; ALEXANDER R. D. &amp; CADE W." pageId="37" pageNumber="442" pagination="375 - 457" refId="ref35864" refString="OTTE D., ALEXANDER R. D. &amp; CADE W. 1987. - The Crickets of New Caledonia (Gryllidae). Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 139: 375 - 457." type="journal article" year="1987">
Otte 
<emphasis box="[132,177,1169,1193]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">et al.</emphasis>
(1987)
</bibRefCitation>
for the New Caledonian species. Small, fusiform species with long FWs and HWs in both sexes. Head more narrow than pronotum (not shown in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Otte" authorityYear="1987" box="[368,452,1223,1246]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Aphonoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="442" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ouveus">
<emphasis box="[368,452,1223,1246]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">A. ouveus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Eyes small but protruding. Ocelli variable (all large and nearly equal in size in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Otte" authorityYear="1987" box="[569,658,1249,1273]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Aphonoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="442" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ouveus">
<emphasis box="[569,658,1249,1273]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">A. ouveus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). TI with a large inner tympanum; outer tympanum lacking or marked by a depression; with two apical spurs. TII with three apical spurs. TIII with three inner and three outer apical spurs, the outers small with the median the longest, the inners longer with the ventral very small and the dorsal the longest (
<bibRefCitation author="OTTE D. &amp; ALEXANDER R. D." box="[398,633,1381,1405]" pageId="37" pageNumber="442" pagination="1 - 477" refId="ref35794" refString="OTTE D. &amp; ALEXANDER R. D. 1983. - Australian crickets. Monographs of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 22: 1 - 477." type="journal article" year="1983">Otte &amp; Alexander 1983</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 277A, B) (not shown in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Otte" authorityYear="1987" box="[272,359,1408,1431]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Aphonoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="442" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ouveus">
<emphasis box="[272,359,1408,1431]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">A. ouveus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); with five to seven outer (five in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Otte" authorityYear="1987" box="[679,766,1408,1431]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Aphonoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="442" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ouveus">
<emphasis box="[679,766,1408,1431]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">A. ouveus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and five to eight inner (six in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Otte" authorityYear="1987" box="[419,508,1434,1458]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Aphonoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="442" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ouveus">
<emphasis box="[419,508,1434,1458]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">A. ouveus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) subapical spurs, small and located in TIII distal half (not shown in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Otte" authorityYear="1987" box="[527,616,1461,1484]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Aphonoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="442" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ouveus">
<emphasis box="[527,616,1461,1484]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">A. ouveus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[130,776,1143,1670]" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[132,189,1487,1511]" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">Male.</emphasis>
No stridulum and no tegminal glands. Male genitalia symmetrical; pseudepiphallic sclerite more or less triangular or rectangular; distal margin more or less deeply emarginate between two setose lobes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[130,776,1143,1670]" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[132,209,1566,1590]" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">Female.</emphasis>
Apex of ovipositor not lanceolate; dorsal valves rounded, ornamented with rounded teeth of variable size (Otte &amp; Alexan- der 1983: fig. 276O-Z). Subgenital plate distal margin straight or somewhat bisinuous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="442" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="37.[132,775,1693,1770]" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">
DISTRIBUTION. — 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chopard" authorityYear="1940" box="[319,425,1693,1717]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Aphonoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="442" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[319,425,1693,1717]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">Aphonoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in 
<collectingCountry box="[593,679,1693,1717]" name="Australia" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">Australia</collectingCountry>
and New 
<collectingCountry box="[132,204,1720,1744]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">Guinea</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="OTTE D. &amp; ALEXANDER R. D." box="[218,449,1720,1744]" pageId="37" pageNumber="442" pagination="1 - 477" refId="ref35794" refString="OTTE D. &amp; ALEXANDER R. D. 1983. - Australian crickets. Monographs of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 22: 1 - 477." type="journal article" year="1983">Otte &amp; Alexander 1983</bibRefCitation>
). As mentioned above, it is represented in 
<collectingCountry box="[227,378,1746,1770]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
by 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Otte" authorityYear="1987" box="[415,588,1746,1770]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Aphonoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="442" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ouveus">
<emphasis box="[415,588,1746,1770]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">Aphonoides ouveus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[132,775,1794,1845]" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">
HABITAT. — According to 
<bibRefCitation author="OTTE D. &amp; ALEXANDER R. D." box="[400,656,1794,1818]" pageId="37" pageNumber="442" pagination="1 - 477" refId="ref35794" refString="OTTE D. &amp; ALEXANDER R. D. 1983. - Australian crickets. Monographs of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 22: 1 - 477." type="journal article" year="1983">Otte &amp; Alexander (1983)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chopard" authorityYear="1940" box="[669,775,1794,1818]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Aphonoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="442" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[669,775,1794,1818]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">Aphonoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may inhabit tree foliage.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="442" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="37.[132,775,1874,2028]" box="[132,222,1874,1900]" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">REMARK</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[132,775,1874,2028]" lastBlockId="37.[811,1455,215,369]" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">
In 
<collectingCountry box="[162,331,1905,1932]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chopard" authorityYear="1940" box="[341,458,1905,1931]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Aphonoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="442" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[341,458,1905,1931]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">Aphonoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known by only one species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Otte, 1987" authorityName="Otte" authorityYear="1987" box="[132,455,1937,1963]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Aphonoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="442" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ouveus">
<emphasis box="[132,325,1937,1963]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">Aphonoides ouveus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="OTTE D. &amp; ALEXANDER R. D. &amp; CADE W." box="[334,455,1937,1963]" pageId="37" pageNumber="442" pagination="375 - 457" refId="ref35864" refString="OTTE D., ALEXANDER R. D. &amp; CADE W. 1987. - The Crickets of New Caledonia (Gryllidae). Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 139: 375 - 457." type="journal article" year="1987">Otte, 1987</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
originating from the 
<collectingRegion country="New Caledonia" name="Province des Iles" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">Loyalty Islands</collectingRegion>
. This species has been transferred to the genus 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">Mistschenkoana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="GOROCHOV A. V." box="[254,428,2001,2027]" pageId="37" pageNumber="442" pagination="3 - 28" refId="ref35061" refString="GOROCHOV A. V. 1990. - New and unsufficiently studied crickets (Orthoptera, Gryllidae) from Vietnam and some other territories. Proceedings of the Zoological Institute RAS 209: 3 - 28. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1990">Gorochov, 1990</bibRefCitation>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="GOROCHOV A. V." box="[464,653,2001,2028]" pageId="37" pageNumber="442" pagination="3 - 28" refId="ref35061" refString="GOROCHOV A. V. 1990. - New and unsufficiently studied crickets (Orthoptera, Gryllidae) from Vietnam and some other territories. Proceedings of the Zoological Institute RAS 209: 3 - 28. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1990">Gorochov (1990)</bibRefCitation>
. Because of the lack of clear distinctive and diagnosic characters, and as we could not examine specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Otte" authorityYear="1987" box="[1162,1354,247,273]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Aphonoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="442" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ouveus">
<emphasis box="[1162,1354,247,273]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">Aphonoides ouveus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we keep this species in its original genus, as hypothesized by 
<bibRefCitation author="OTTE D. &amp; ALEXANDER R. D." pageId="37" pageNumber="442" pagination="1 - 477" refId="ref35794" refString="OTTE D. &amp; ALEXANDER R. D. 1983. - Australian crickets. Monographs of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 22: 1 - 477." type="journal article" year="1983">Otte &amp; Alexander (1983)</bibRefCitation>
. The monophyly of both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chopard" authorityYear="1940" box="[1290,1407,311,337]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Aphonoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="442" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1290,1407,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">Aphonoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[813,977,343,369]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="442">Mistschenkoana</emphasis>
will have to be checked.
</paragraph>
